Children will feel joyful to learn a new lesson with each story
The Inside Story Of Clown Fish
One day, Jester, the Clown Fish got caught in a net and ended up in a Fish Pet Shop. He was put into a fish tank next to the gold fish. There were all kinds of fish in the shop. A boy knocked on Jester's tank. Jester fled at the back of the tank and hid behind a coral. "Mom, I want this one. It's funny," the boy exclaimed. Soon, Jester found himself in a new environment altogether. His new tank and new environment were different.
He was given food particles to eat. Jester fell homesick. Seeing Jester's condition, the boy cried and decided to put him back into the sea. His father helped him drop Jester into the water. Jester quickly swam home. From then on, he was careful not to get caught in nets.
6
The Inside Story Of Honeybee
It was spring time and the Queen Bee had laid her eggs. Bumble, with the rest of the workers, had been assigned different duties. Highlighted in the duty roaster, Bumble had been assigned to attend to the Queen. She was very thrilled. Bumble gave the Queen a sponge bath and helped her into the silver gown. By the time the Queen was ready, the babies woke up. Bumble fed them and then served supper to the Queen.
She wished her good night and went on to the next assignment. Feeling hungry after a long day's hard work Bumble quenched her thirst with nectar. Then she flew into the garden for fresh air and resumed her work of collecting pollen.
